59.4	Sweatshop	Sweatshop	Sweatshop (or sweat factory) is a negatively connoted term for any working environment considered to be unacceptably difficult or dangerous. Sweatshop workers often work long hours for very low pay, regardless of laws mandating overtime pay or a minimum wage. Child labour laws may be violated. Sweatshops may have hazardous materials and situations. Employees may be subject to employer abuse without an easy way, if any way, to protect themselves.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Sweatshop_in_Ludlow_Street_Tenement%2C_New_York_cph.3a24271.jpg/220px-Sweatshop_in_Ludlow_Street_Tenement%2C_New_York_cph.3a24271.jpg
